properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 6 at 1:03PM PST until January 7 at 6:09PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Seattle has issued a flood warning
for the following rivers in Washington...

Tolt River Above Carnation affecting King County


Heavy rain and rising snow levels will allow sufficient storm runoff
to drive the Tolt River above flood stage evening.

The National Weather Service in Seattle has issued a

* Flood Warning for
The Tolt River Above Carnation
* from this afternoon to Tuesday evening.
* At 12:15 PM Monday the flow was 1514 cfs.
* Flood flow is 5000 cfs.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river will rise above flood flow around 4 PM Monday
and crest near 6304 cfs around 10 PM Monday. The river will fall
below flood flow Tuesday morning.
* Impact...At 5000 cfs, the Tolt River will flood Tolt River Rd NE and
many driveways. Some homes in the San Souci area could be
inaccessible due to deep and quick flood waters. This river level
on the Tolt corresponds to a phase 3 flood in the King County flood
system.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
